model

Class Screening

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.Screening

  • public class Screening
extends java.lang.Object
    Explanation: This file holds all columns of the 'screening' table. It contains private variables for each column, a constructor to initialize them, and getters and setters for each. The variables are created as properties. "A Property notifies us when any variable such as name, last name, etc. is changed. This helps us keep the view in sync with the data." (SW Test Academy) References: http://www.swtestacademy.com/database-operat√§ions-javafx/ https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H1mePFyqqiE&t=18s
